2a8bc31f-5e43-4261-9fb0-b7dd62acafb9.label: Ulman critically links physical appearance to professional success, pointing out that an artwork's value can escalate based on the artist's perceived beauty or social media followers. This observation underscores the pervasive "electronic economy of looking good," where commercial and cultural values are inextricably tied to curated self-presentation.
